<br>
First of all Lautrec, no one should be sending you ugly tells.  That is wrong on a lot of levels, and if it continues let ME know about it and I will resolve it for you.  People may not agree with you, but that is no reason for harrassment.<br>
<br>
Second of all Lautrec, you are not making friends here.  You have managed to insult virtually all of KCoG's past and current leadership.  That requires some effort, and is a dubiously impressive mark.  Unfortunately it is not the way to proceed if you want to actually change things.  A lot of people's statements you have maybe read wrong or are deliberately twisting.  For instance peoples numerous attempts to explain to you that bards are charisma based.  Yes, they actually get their mana pool from int, but virtually all the songs they use are given a resist rate off of your charisma, so that having a high charisma will help you much more than having a high int.  That is what they meant when they said that bards are charisma based rather than int based.  That is like a Paladin saying that since he gets his mana from Wisdom that wisdom is the only stat he should work on, when really it is a secondary important stat because he really needs the melee based stats more.  Also you should not ignore those that have more experience than you.  For instance Lagdalen who you have insulted several times in this thread, is not only a previous dragon leader, but also has a (I believe) 53 Bard named Vree.  Among numerous other alts in the 50's.  I would really really be surprised if you knew game dynamics better than her, because she has been playing for a long time.<br>
<br>
Frankly, telling you which all/all items you are allowed to roll for is our job.  You can wear whatever you want, but when it comes down to it, we have to make this as fair to as many people so we WILL restrict rolls to make it fair as such.  I have trouble believing that you cannot understand this concept after being in an alliance like SB.  SB restricts the items the same way, so why are you not blasting people there with this stuff?  I am sure Rbecka (a leader I have a lot of respect for) would be interested in hearing your arguments and dismissing them much more abrubtly than we have here.  Throwing in the &quot;it's people like you who ruin the experience for myself and others&quot; is not only a low blow, but it is inaccurate and can be twisted around other ways.  For instance I might say the same thing about you, because you are not willing to step back and look at it from a leadership standpoint, you are only willing to look at it from what you could possibly gain from it.  So what gives you the right to ruin my experience?  Obviously I have to deal with things like that, so it gets much more complicated, but when you deal with just the base reality you are being just as unfair to me as I am to you.<br>
<br>
I do not hold any grudge, or anything like that. Nor should anyone else (/em looks around the room daring a response).  You are welcome to come on further raids with us, and there will be no hard feelings.  Just remember, that other people want to be able to win stuff besides bards, and sometimes you just have to look at the whole picture.  Incidentally if you do not want to be insulted, you might want to look at holding your tongue sometimes, and not insulting others, especially those like Lagdalen, Kommisar, Haemish, and others who have earned our respect many times over.  I have a feeling that is the reason behind whoever it was that sent you that tell, and despite the fact that it was inappropriate for that person to do so, you might want to look at why they felt the need.<br>
