Do not ask questions, during or after a CoG raid.<br>
<br>
Although the leaders appear to be saying that they invite comment and constructive criticism, they actually seem to thrive on ridiculing and antagonizing the person who asked a very real question arising from a very real concern.<br>
<br>
I am behind the Bard, when he says you are ignoring the concern here.<br>
<br>
There also seems to be a great deal of misinformation about the relationship between int/wis and mana.<br>
Having 9 characters on 3 servers, only 2 do not have casting ability, I can tell you that int and wis are the stats that increase the mana pool, Which is what this bard is looking for.  Cha is great when casting to prevent resists by the mob.  But it is my understanding that mana regen spells do not help bards, only flowing thought items help, which are mighty hard to come by until you are upper level.  This means that a bard needs an expanded mana pool, so that he can continue to play needed tunes for the benefit of the entire group, through-out the fight.<br>
<br>
I am not surprised that the liaison would be party to this misinformation, since this has been his history for the past 12 months that I have been playing.  I have seen him tell people that certain areas were not safe, that you could not go in them until you were in the upper levels ( I think this was because he didn't want to go in), I have seen him argue with others in other posts, and on e-mails.  He has been known to make threats and create problems for people in the game.<br>
i.e. running to an ex-guildmates new guilds and making trouble for them, by telling untruths and embellishments and twisting their words.I will not name names, but he should know who they are.<br>
<br>
Much of what the Bard had said was valid, and who are these leaders, who know so much more than Varent about who should have or use items. All/All is about as self-explanatory as it gets.  I agree that you read what is written but you don't hear what is being said.<br>
<br>
To humiliate and belittle another, for the way they chose to play their characters is childish and irresponsible, especially when you call yourself leaders.<br>
It is not the bard who should apologize for asking a simple question but the leaders who have all handled this so badly.<br>
<br>
When it appeared that you had all run out of new material you even resorted to dragging in SD and the guild leaders, to take this one individual to task, after you egged it on and made threats and insults to him.<br>
<br>
I am sure that there will be some response to this, and having seen what some of you are capable of, I fully expect that I will be in some way threatened, or black -balled by you.<br>
<br>
Not to worry!  I do not let things upset me to any degree.  I do not desire to be part of your little political tyranny, and will avoid CoG raids in the future.  And, by all means, if I question anything at all, it will be silent.<br>
<br>
Good Leaders are hard to come by, seems like those in power at CoG and many of the Alliances have earned their position by being unfair, antagonistic and hostile.<br>
<br>
I fully expect to get flamed big-time for this, but then that would prove my point about the leaders, wouldn't it?<br>
<br>
Shei Mysticmoon<br>
Level 24 Wizard<br>
